    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-07-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="706"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d706">
                <head>No. 702.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-07-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 29, 1881</date>. (Received August
                        18.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 430.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my No. 400, concerning the proposed
                    emigration of the widow Olivier and her young children, I have the honor to
                    inclose herewith copies of a further correspondence between the council of
                    Bourgeoisie of Neuveville and this legation.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>NICHOLAS FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure 1 in No. 430.—Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <gloss type="from">Council of Bourgeoisie of Neuveville</gloss> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Neuveville</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-07-25">
                                <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 25, 1881</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Concerning the emigration of the woman
                        Olivier and her children, about whom we had the honor to write you on the
                        26th of April last, and to which you had the kindness to reply, we take the
                        liberty to submit to you the inclosed declaration asking you to inform us
                        whether, upon the production of this document, the authorities <pb
                            facs="1291" n="1167" xml:id="pg_1167"/> of New York will create
                        difficulties to <hi rend="italic">permit</hi> said woman to continue her
                        journey to her destination.</p>
                    <p>You will excuse us, sir, hut desiring to allay the difficulties which might
                        arise concerning this family, we desire to he informed on this point.</p>
                    <p>In begging you to accept our thanks in advance, we tender you the assurance
                        of our distinguished consideration.</p>
                    <p>In the name of the Council of Bourgeoisie.</p>
                    <p>The secretary.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>CESAR WYSS.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Accompaniment to inclosure 1 in No.
                            430.—Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <p>We, the undersigned, hereby bind ourselves to receive and provide for the
                        widow Mrs. Maria Olivier and her children in case they come to America.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <list>
                                <item>JACOB REEF.</item>
                                <item>FRIED. SCHÜPBACH.</item>
                                <item>ELIZABETH KAHIN.</item>
                                <item>BENEDICT EUCH.</item>
                                <item>JAKOB HEINZMANN.</item>
                                <item>ALBERT WIDMER.</item>
                                <item>JACOB EUCH.</item>
                                <item>JAKOB HAFELI.</item>
                                <item>FRED. LEISER.</item>
                            </list>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                    <postscript>
                        <p rend="flushleft">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wetzel County, West Virginia</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Clerk’s Office, County Court:</hi>
                        </p>
                        <p>I, John C. McEldonnell, clerk of the county court of Wetzel County, in
                            the State of West Virginia, do hereby certify that I am well acquainted
                            with Frederick Sehüp, bach, Jacob Reef, Benedict Euch, Jacob Hintzmann,
                            Albert Widmer, Jacob Euch, Jacob Haferle, and Frederick Leiser, whose
                            names are signed to the within instrument of writing, and know them to
                            be good citizens, careful and responsible men, and in my opinion will do
                            and perform any contract they may enter into. Given under my hand and
                            official seal this 28th day of June, 1881.</p>
                        <closer>[<hi rend="smallcaps">seal.</hi>] <signed>JOHN C. McELDONNELL,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Cleric County Court, Wetzel County, West
                                    Virginia.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </postscript>
                </frus:attachment>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure 2 in No. 430.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to the <gloss
                                type="to">Council of Bourgeoisie</gloss>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Berne</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-07-27">
                                <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 27, 1881</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gentlemen</hi>: Your letter of 25th instant, inclosing
                        a document relative to the widow Mrs. Maria Olivier and her children, is
                        received.</p>
                    <p>This legation cannot undertake to say what view the authorities at New York
                        may take as to the sufficiency of the document in question, and in no event
                        can the legation assure you that the widow and her children will be exempt
                        from the customary examination on landing in the United States.</p>
                    <p>The facts of the case, as set forth in the previous correspondence, have been
                        made known to the emigration authorities.</p>
                    <p>Returning the document you inclosed for examination,</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>NICHOLAS FISH.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
